        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 32
miles east of Ranch Campground, or 33 miles east of Ursine. This
storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central Iron
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
